<subSubSection pageId="26" pageNumber="25" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="26.[192,1286,643,699]" pageId="26" pageNumber="25">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,335,643,667]" pageId="26" pageNumber="25">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
In members of this species the elytra are mostly dark blue; the disc shows transverse fascia, one on the anterior margin and the other behind the middle.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="26.[1307,1440,643,667]" box="[1307,1440,643,667]" pageId="26" pageNumber="25">two yellow</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="26" pageNumber="25" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="26.[192,1441,739,1147]" pageId="26" pageNumber="25">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,396,739,763]" pageId="26" pageNumber="25">Redescription.</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[406,464,739,762]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="25">Size:</emphasis>
Length 10.5 mm; width 5.0 mm. 
<emphasis box="[889,963,740,763]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="25">Form:</emphasis>
As in 
<figureCitation box="[1047,1137,739,763]" captionStart="Figures 45-48" captionStartId="34.[192,287,1894,1916]" captionTargetBox="[231,1408,243,1863]" captionTargetId="figure-15@34.[221,1408,192,1869]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="Figures 45-48. Habitus of Chariessa spp. 45) Chariessa floridana. 46) C. pilosa. 47) C. pilosa. 48) C. ramicornis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5169162" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5169162/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="25">Fig. 48</figureCitation>
. Mouthparts testaceous, except mandibles brown; antennae bicolored, capitulum black, remainder testaceous; cranium and pronotum black, with a bluish luster; mesothorax castaneous, pterothorax, legs, and abdomen testaceous; mesoscutellum black; elytra mostly black, with a bluish luster, with two narrow fasciae, one at anterior margin, the other behind middle. 
<emphasis box="[726,791,867,891]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="25">Head</emphasis>
: Funicular antennomeres progressively shorter and wider towards capitulum, capitulum longer than combined length of funicular antennomeres, capitular antennomeres 9 and 10 with collateral branch (
<figureCitation box="[775,907,931,955]" captionStart="Figures 1-18" captionStartId="6.[192,287,1779,1801]" captionTargetBox="[211,1412,192,1754]" captionTargetId="figure-16@6.[211,1421,192,1764]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figures 1-18. Antennae of Chariessa spp. 1) Chariessa duponti (male). 2) C. duponti (female). 3) C. floridana (male). 4) C. floridana (female). 5) C. catalina (male). 6) C. catalina (female). 7) C. elegans (male). 8) C. elegans (female). 9) C. texana (male). 10) C. dichroa (male). 11) C. dichroa (female). 12) C. pilosa (male). 13) C. pilosa (female). 14) C. ramicornis (male). 15) C. ramicornis (female). 16) C. vestita (male). 17) C. vestita (female). 18) C. texana (female)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5169148" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5169148/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="25">Fig. 14, 15</figureCitation>
), antennomere 11 oblong; eyes small, frons wider than width of eye (EW/FW 35/20). 
<emphasis box="[702,791,963,987]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="25">Thorax</emphasis>
: Pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[951,1038,963,987]" captionStart="Figures 21-29" captionStartId="9.[192,286,1590,1612]" captionTargetBox="[221,1399,228,1562]" captionTargetId="figure-57@9.[192,1441,192,1572]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figures 21-29. Pronota of Chariessa spp. 21) Chariessa catalina. 22) C. elegans. 23) C. ramicornis. 24) C. duponti. 25) C. floridana. 26) C. texana. 27) C. dichroa. 28) C. pilosa. 29) C. vestita." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5169156" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5169156/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="25">Fig. 23</figureCitation>
) transverse (PW/PL 95/85), side margins evenly arcuate, disc finely punctate; elytral asetiferous punctation small, profusely distributed throughout disc (EL/EW 230/75); protibial anterior margin spinous. 
<emphasis box="[1053,1167,1027,1051]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="25">Abdomen</emphasis>
: Pygidium scutiform; aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[316,399,1059,1083]" captionStart="Figures 63-65" captionStartId="38.[192,287,1626,1648]" captionTargetBox="[192,1444,212,1608]" captionTargetId="figure-16@38.[192,1445,192,1608]" captionTargetPageId="38" captionText="Figures 63-65. Male genitalia and aedeagi. 63) Chariessa ramicornis. 64) C. texana. 65) C. vestita." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5169176" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5169176/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="25">Fig. 63</figureCitation>
) poorly sclerotized ventrally; phallobasic lobes slightly developed, fimbriate, phallobasic rod long, linear, phallobasic apodeme broad; phallus with subapical sclerotization, phallic apex triangular/subacuminate.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="26.[192,954,1187,1211]" box="[192,954,1187,1211]" pageId="26" pageNumber="25">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,411,1187,1211]" pageId="26" pageNumber="25">Natural history.</emphasis>
A specimen was collected during November.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="26.[192,903,1251,1275]" box="[192,903,1251,1275]" pageId="26" pageNumber="25">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,329,1251,1275]" pageId="26" pageNumber="25">Variation.</emphasis>
Size: Length 10.0-14.5 mm; width 4.8-7.0 mm.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
